## [FAIL] CRITICAL — A3 detection condition requires `leadOnSlide: true` on no-grid Slide 1, but spec never says to set it

**What is missing:**
A3 specifies: "SlideTemplate-Detection-Condition für no-grid-cover: `slide.kind === "text" && slide.isFirst && slide.leadOnSlide === true`". The spec also asserts: "Nach A2 ist `leadOnSlide: true` NUR auf no-grid-Slide-1."

But currently no-grid Slide 1 is produced with `leadOnSlide: undefined` (not set at all — see `splitAgendaIntoSlides` line 487: `rawSlides.push({ kind: "text", blocks: slidesWithChunks[0] ?? [] })`). Neither `splitAgendaIntoSlides` nor `buildManualSlides` sets `leadOnSlide: true` for the no-grid case.

**What a developer will implement (two bad outcomes):**

*Outcome A (follows A3 detection condition literally):* Changes the template condition from `slide.isFirst` to `slide.isFirst && slide.leadOnSlide === true`. Since `leadOnSlide` is never `true` on no-grid Slide 1, the entire Hashtags+Title+Lead block disappears — broken no-grid rendering.

*Outcome B (keeps `slide.isFirst` condition):* A3's "eindeutige Detection" claim is never implemented, `leadOnSlide` plays no role in no-grid Slide 1 detection, and the template diverges silently from the spec.

**Spec must add:** Both `splitAgendaIntoSlides` (no-grid path, Slide 0 push) and `buildManualSlides` (no-grid Slide 0) must set `leadOnSlide: true` when `!hasGrid && slide.isFirst`. Files-to-Change table must list these specific lines.

