## [FAIL] HIGH — `GRID_MAX_HEIGHT = 700` needs recalculation; Hashtags now appear BELOW the grid

**What is missing:**
The comment for `GRID_MAX_HEIGHT` documents: "Derived as: 1350 - 2×80 (padding) - 34 (HeaderRow) - 32+62 (hashtags + HASHTAGS_TO_TITLE_GAP, when present) - ~280 (worst-case 3-line title) - 48 (TITLE_TO_GRID_GAP) ≈ 750. Round down to 700."

After A1, Hashtags move from ABOVE the title (consuming 32+62=94px before the grid) to BELOW the grid. The available height for the grid now includes the Hashtags area, but must also account for the Lead above the grid. New budget:
- Old elements above Grid: Header(34) + Hashtags(~32+gap) + Title(~280) + TITLE_TO_GRID_GAP(48) = ~394px
- New elements above Grid: Header(34) + Title(~280) + Title→Lead gap + Lead(~2-line≈126px) + Lead→Grid gap

With Lead above the grid and Hashtags below, keeping `GRID_MAX_HEIGHT = 700` risks the Grid + Hashtags row overflowing the canvas on items with Leads.

**What a developer will implement:**
Will leave `GRID_MAX_HEIGHT = 700` as-is. On a 3-image item with a 2-line Lead, the rendered PNG may clip Hashtags or push them off-canvas. Visual Smoke E5 should catch this — but only if tested with a long lead.

**Spec must add:** New `GRID_MAX_HEIGHT` calculation comment and value that accounts for Lead above the grid and Hashtags below.

