## [INFO] LOW — `instagram/route.ts` "pre-DB check entfernen" is misleading; no such check exists

The Files to Change entry says "pre-DB check entfernen, post-DB silent-clamp" for `instagram/route.ts`. The current code has **no** `MAX_BODY_IMAGE_COUNT` pre-DB check in that route — only a post-DB `Math.min(requestedImages, availableImages)`. The "entfernen" instruction is a false reference that will confuse the developer. The actual change needed is just adding `MAX_GRID_IMAGES` to the existing `Math.min` call. No removal needed.

